# GRBPWR Products Manager — Project Overview

## What This Project Is

**grbpwr-products-manager** is a Go backend service that powers the **GRBPWR** fashion e-commerce platform. It serves as the complete backend API handling product catalog management, order processing, payment integration, analytics, and content management for a clothing brand storefront.

**Module path:** `github.com/jekabolt/grbpwr-manager`
**Go version:** 1.26+
**Database:** MySQL (via `sqlx` + `golang-migrate`)
**API transport:** gRPC with gRPC-Gateway (REST/JSON over HTTP)

---

## Architecture Overview

```
cmd/main.go          → CLI entrypoint (cobra)
  └─ app/app.go      → Application bootstrap & lifecycle
       ├─ internal/apisrv/admin/      → Admin gRPC service (JWT-protected)
       ├─ internal/apisrv/frontend/   → Public frontend gRPC service
       ├─ internal/apisrv/auth/       → Authentication service (JWT)
       ├─ internal/api/http/          → HTTP server (gRPC-Gateway + Swagger UI)
       ├─ internal/store/             → MySQL data access layer
       ├─ internal/payment/stripe/    → Stripe payment processing
       ├─ internal/mail/              → Transactional email (Resend API)
       ├─ internal/bucket/            → S3-compatible media storage (MinIO)
       ├─ internal/cache/             → In-memory dictionary/settings cache
       ├─ internal/analytics/         → GA4 + BigQuery analytics pipeline
       └─ internal/dependency/        → Interface definitions (contracts)
```

### Key Design Patterns

- **Interface-driven architecture:** All major subsystems are defined as interfaces in [`internal/dependency/dependency.go`](internal/dependency/dependency.go). The [`Repository`](internal/dependency/dependency.go:390) interface is the central data access contract.
- **Dependency injection:** [`app.App`](app/app.go:41) wires all dependencies at startup and passes them to service constructors.
- **Proto-first API design:** All API contracts are defined in `.proto` files under `proto/`, generating Go code, gRPC stubs, REST gateway handlers, and Swagger docs.
- **Background workers:** Several goroutine-based workers run alongside the API server:
  - **Order cleanup** — expires stuck/abandoned orders
  - **Stripe reconciliation** — cleans orphaned pre-order PaymentIntents
  - **GA4 sync** — periodically fetches analytics from GA4/BigQuery and caches locally
  - **Mail worker** — async email queue processing

