## API Layer

### Three gRPC Services

1. **`AuthService`** ([`proto/auth/auth/auth.proto`](proto/auth/auth/auth.proto)) — Login, create/delete admin users, change password. Routes: `/api/auth/*`

2. **`AdminService`** ([`proto/admin/admin/admin.proto`](proto/admin/admin/admin.proto)) — JWT-protected admin operations. Routes: `/api/admin/*`
   - Product CRUD, stock management, stock change history
   - Order management (list, refund, cancel, deliver, tracking, custom orders)
   - Promo code management
   - Hero/homepage content management
   - Archive (lookbook) management
   - Site settings (shipping carriers, payment methods, announcements)
   - Support ticket management
   - Business metrics & analytics dashboard
   - Media/content upload (images, videos)

3. **`FrontendService`** (defined in `proto/frontend/`) — Public storefront API. Routes: `/api/frontend/*`
   - Product catalog browsing (paged, filtered, sorted)
   - Order submission with Stripe pre-order PaymentIntent flow
   - Order lookup by UUID + email
   - Order cancellation/return by customer
   - Newsletter subscribe/unsubscribe
   - Back-in-stock notifications (NotifyMe / waitlist)
   - Archive browsing
   - Support ticket submission
   - Dictionary (categories, sizes, colors, etc.)

### API Transport

- gRPC services are exposed as **REST/JSON** via **gRPC-Gateway** annotations in proto files
- Swagger UI served at the HTTP endpoint for API documentation
- HTTP server configured in [`internal/api/http/`](internal/api/http/) with CORS, health checks

