## Build & Development

### Prerequisites

- Go 1.26+
- `buf` (protobuf toolchain)
- `protoc-gen-go`, `protoc-gen-go-grpc`, `protoc-gen-grpc-gateway`, `protoc-gen-openapiv2`
- `mockery` v2.52+ (mock generation)
- `oapi-codegen` (OpenAPI client generation)
- `libwebp-dev` (WebP image processing)

### Key Make Targets

```bash
make init          # Clean + install tools + generate protos + generate mocks
make build         # Full build (proto + mocks + swagger + binary)
make build-quick   # Build without mock regeneration
make run           # Build and run (sources .env)
make proto         # Regenerate protobuf code
make generate-mocks # Regenerate mockery mocks
make lint          # Run golangci-lint
make cov           # Run tests with coverage
make image         # Build Docker image
```

### Docker

Multi-stage Dockerfile: builder stage generates protos, mocks, swagger, and compiles the binary. Runtime image is Alpine with `libwebp` and `ca-certificates`.

### Testing

- Unit tests use **mockery**-generated mocks from `internal/dependency/mocks/`
- Test files are co-located with source (`*_test.go`)
- Integration tests connect to MySQL (see `internal/store/mysql_test.go`)

